The end goal workflow of the gem:
- "lazy-translate [source path] [config_path]


1.
  %p Some text
2.
  %p
    Some long long
    long long text
3.
  %p
    Some long
    %strong text
    with
    %em some html
4.
  %p
    Some text
    = some_var
    with variables
5.
  %p
    = link_to('Text inside link', path)
    = image_tag 'Text inside any call', img
6.
  %p
    img{alt: 'Text inside attributes'}


1. ToFileType.for_source.from_path
   ToFileType.for_config.from_path
   ToSourceFileType.from_path
   ToConfigFileType.from_path

2. ConfigHashAppendix, ConfigUpdater(hash, file)

3. SourceUpdater(text, text_elements, file_type)

4. SourceFileReader(text, type) => ConfigHashAppendix(key_name => key_content), TextElements

5. Output ConfigHashAppendix, Source file diff. Prompt for write\copy.

6. Reorder folders and files

7. Complex HAML parser tasks

8. HAML Parser (Haml::Parser => TextElements)

9. ERB Parser

10. Rubocop

11. More args

12. License, Readme, Travis, Codeclimate
